def intersect(ray, sphere):
    origin = ray[0]
    direction = ray[1]
    center = sphere[0]
    radius = sphere[1]
    
    a = dot(direction, direction)
    b = 2 * dot(direction, origin - center)
    c = dot(origin - center, origin - center) - radius**2
    
    discriminant = b**2 - 4*a*c
    if discriminant < 0:
        return None
    
    t = (-b - sqrt(discriminant)) / (2*a)
    return origin + t * direction
